                        "type": "0",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "An elderly client is being seen at the primary health care provider's (PHCP's) office. The client is thin and has multiple bruises on exposed skin, and the nurse suspects elder neglect and abuse. The client's caregiver does all the talking and updates the nurse about the client since last being seen. The nurse would take which best action?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nElder abuse and neglect is a concern. Health care professionals are mandated reporters. If there is a suspicion of elder abuse, it must be investigated and reported. The nurse would try to follow up with the client privately to confirm suspicions. Option 1 may produce fear in the client, especially if the caregiver is present and is the abuser. Options 2 and 3 are not client focused and place focus on the caregiver providing information and care to the elderly client.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the subject, that the nurse suspects abuse and neglect. Note the strategic word, best. Read each option carefully and think about the usefulness of each action. Noting the word privately in option 4 will direct you to this option.",
